ZH: 子孙是家族的延续。
EN: Descendants are the continuation of a family.

ZH: 我对我的子孙充满了期望。
EN: I have high expectations for my descendants.

ZH: 这座古老的村庄有许多子孙在此定居。
EN: Many descendants have settled in this ancient village.

ZH: 我希望我的子孙能够继承我的事业。
EN: I hope my descendants can inherit my career.

ZH: 子孙的成就是父辈的骄傲。
EN: The achievements of the descendants are the pride of the previous generations.

ZH: 这些孩子是我们的子孙。
EN: These children are our descendants.

ZH: 子孙的未来需要我们的关怀和指导。
EN: The future of the descendants requires our care and guidance.

ZH: 长辈们希望看到子孙们过上幸福的生活。
EN: The elders hope to see the descendants live a happy life.

ZH: 子孙需要明白他们的家族历史和文化传承。
EN: Descendants need to understand their family history and cultural heritage.

ZH: 每一个子孙都应该感到自豪。
EN: Every descendant should feel proud.

ZH: 子孙们聚集在一起庆祝家族团聚。
EN: Descendants gather together to celebrate family reunion.

ZH: 我们要为子孙留下美好的环境。
EN: We need to leave a good environment for our descendants.

ZH: 老人们传授着子孙们尊敬长辈的价值观念。
EN: The elderly pass on the values of respecting elders to the descendants.

ZH: 子孙们要铭记先辈的艰辛付出。
EN: Descendants should remember the hardships and sacrifices of their ancestors.

ZH: 子孙们继承了家族的优秀传统。
EN: The descendants have inherited the excellent traditions of the family.

ZH: 祖辈们的智慧将传承给子孙一代。
EN: The wisdom of the ancestors will be passed down to the next generation.

ZH: 子孙们将继续追寻家族的梦想。
EN: The descendants will continue to pursue the family's dreams.

ZH: 子孙们的成长是对祖辈们最好的回报。
EN: The growth of the descendants is the best reward for the ancestors.

ZH: 子孙们要珍惜家族的传统和价值观。
EN: Descendants should cherish the family's traditions and values.

ZH: 祖辈们的故事是子孙们的灵感源泉。
EN: The stories of the ancestors are the source of inspiration for the descendants.
